The paper discusses swarm robotics, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO) that focuses on the coordination of multiple robots to achieve a common goal. The paper also discusses the software and hardware components required for swarming, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.MA), systems and control (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) for simulating and testing new swarming behaviors.
